The Zondo commission will continue to hear Transnet related evidence from the Executive Manager in the Finance department of Transnet Freight Rail, Mr Yousuf Laher JOHANNESBURG - Transnet finance executive, Yousuf Laher, will continue his testimony before the state capture inquiry on Thursday. Laher was part of a team that worked on two controversial tenders, one for over 1,000 trains and another for 100 locomotives. WATCH: Transnet in the spotlight again at state capture inquiry Laher was implicated by former colleague Francis Callard. Callard told the commission that Laher asked him to draft a memorandum to increase the cost of the locomotives. Laher is expected to respond to the allegations.